```markdown
# üåü Light Seeker ‚Äì The Path of Giving

A minimal spiritual web game built with HTML, CSS and JavaScript.

This static single-page game includes four scenes:
1. Village ‚Äî a monk asks if you will share your light.
2. Marketplace ‚Äî help a merchant set up a donation box.
3. Temple ‚Äî make a symbolic offering.
4. Light ‚Äî receive a blessing and see a UPI QR and copy-to-clipboard.

Enhancements:
- EN / ‡§π‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§¶‡•Ä language toggle
- Feedback modal (EmailJS integration + mailto fallback)
- Smooth scene transitions and UI animations

Project structure
- index.html
- style.css
- script.js
- assets/
  - upi-qr.png  (add your QR image here)
- README.md
- LICENSE
- .gitignore

Before publishing
1. Replace the placeholder UPI ID in index.html (input#upiId value) with your real UPI ID.
2. Put your QR image at assets/upi-qr.png (PNG or SVG).
3. (Optional) Configure EmailJS: edit script.js and set EMAILJS_USER_ID, EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID, EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID.

Create & publish (quick commands)
1. In your terminal (inside the project folder) run:
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit ‚Äî Light Seeker"
2. Create repo & push (using GitHub CLI):
   gh repo create lightpath9-game --public --source=. --remote=origin --push
   (replace --public with --private if needed)
3. Enable Pages in the repo settings:
   - Go to GitHub ‚Üí Repo ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Pages
   - Source: main branch ‚Üí /root ‚Üí Save
   - Site will be available at: https://<your-username>.github.io/lightpath9-game/

If you don't use gh CLI:
- Create a repo on github.com named lightpath9-game, then:
  git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/lightpath9-game.git
  git branch -M main
  git push -u origin main

Notes
- This project is static and easy to host on GitHub Pages or Netlify.
- Do not publish sensitive credentials in script.js. Use EmailJS or a backend for secure email sending.
```
